"use strict";(self.webpackChunkpos_doc=self.webpackChunkpos_doc||[]).push([[566],{4068(t,e,a){a.r(e),a.d(e,{_pageData:()=>o,default:()=>r});var i=a(641);const o=JSON.parse('{"path":"/guide/variation-layouts.html","title":"Variation Card Layouts","lang":"en-US","frontmatter":{"title":"Variation Card Layouts","description":"Learn how to configure and use multiple variation card layouts (Card, Table, and List views) in WooCommerce POS."},"git":{},"filePathRelative":"guide/variation-layouts.md"}'),s={name:"variation-layouts.md"},r=(0,a(6262).A)(s,[["render",function(t,e,a,o,s,r){return(0,i.uX)(),(0,i.CE)("div",null,[...e[0]||(e[0]=[(0,i.Fv)('<h1 id="variation-card-layouts" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#variation-card-layouts"><span>Variation Card Layouts</span></a></h1><h2 id="introduction" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#introduction"><span>Introduction</span></a></h2><p>Many products in WooCommerce feature multiple options like sizes, colors, and materials. Managing these variations quickly at the checkout counter is essential for efficient order entry.</p><p>WooCommerce Point of Sale (POS) includes a customizable <strong>Variation Selection Layout</strong> system. This allows store managers and cashiers to choose how product variations are displayed inside the selection pane, matching the layout structure to the specific type of inventory.</p><p>This page explains how to configure variation views in the admin backend and details each layout mode.</p><hr><h2 id="layout-configurations" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#layout-configurations"><span>Layout Configurations</span></a></h2><h3 id="section-1-variation-view-configuration" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#section-1-variation-view-configuration"><span>Section 1: Variation View Configuration</span></a></h3><p>Store administrators can configure the default presentation style for variable products globally. To set the default layout:</p><ol><li>Log in to the WordPress Admin Panel.</li><li>Navigate to <strong>Point of Sale</strong> &gt; <strong>Settings</strong> &gt; <strong>Products</strong>.</li><li>Locate the <strong>Product Variation View</strong> option.</li><li>Select your preferred default display mode: <strong>Card View</strong>, <strong>Table View</strong>, or <strong>List View</strong>.</li><li>Save the configuration changes.</li></ol><p><img src="/pos-for-woocommerce/images/woocommerce-pos/productvariationviewadmin.webp" alt="Variation View Configuration"></p><hr><h3 id="section-2-card-view" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#section-2-card-view"><span>Section 2: Card View</span></a></h3><p>The <strong>Card View</strong> displays variations as a visual grid of thumbnail tiles. When a cashier clicks on a variable product, they are presented with large visual cards containing images and attribute labels.</p><ul><li><strong>Visual Selection Experience:</strong> This mode is highly interactive and visually descriptive, making it easy to identify options by color, pattern, or aesthetic design.</li><li><strong>Ideal for:</strong> Apparel, footwear, accessories, and products where physical appearance is the primary differentiator.</li></ul><p><img src="/pos-for-woocommerce/images/woocommerce-pos/variationcard.webp" alt="Card View Layout"></p><hr><h3 id="section-3-table-view" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#section-3-table-view"><span>Section 3: Table View</span></a></h3><p>The <strong>Table View</strong> presents variations in a structured database-style grid with multiple columns. Cashiers can view detailed attributes, SKUs, exact pricing, and live stock counts side-by-side.</p><ul><li><strong>Detailed Comparison Layout:</strong> Cashiers get full data density on a single screen, allowing them to compare quantities and prices at a glance.</li><li><strong>Ideal for:</strong> Wholesalers, industrial parts, building materials, and high-volume counters where cashiers need quick access to technical details and stock numbers.</li></ul><p><img src="/pos-for-woocommerce/images/woocommerce-pos/variationtable.webp" alt="Table View Layout"></p><hr><h3 id="section-4-list-view" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#section-4-list-view"><span>Section 4: List View</span></a></h3><p>The <strong>List View</strong> displays variations in a clean, vertical stack of simple text rows. Each row shows the variation attribute and a clear selection button.</p><ul><li><strong>Compact Selection:</strong> Reduces visual clutter and helps cashiers navigate through simple choice lists without thumbnail distractions or wide column tables.</li><li><strong>Ideal for:</strong> Electronics (e.g., storage capacity or RAM options), software licenses, and basic sizes where simple text labels are sufficient.</li></ul><p><img src="/pos-for-woocommerce/images/woocommerce-pos/variationlist.webp" alt="List View Layout"></p><hr><h2 id="variation-layouts-comparison" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#variation-layouts-comparison"><span>Variation Layouts Comparison</span></a></h2><p>The table below contrasts the features and best fits for each layout option:</p><table><thead><tr><th style="text-align:left;">Layout Mode</th><th style="text-align:left;">Best Use Case</th><th style="text-align:left;">Advantages</th><th style="text-align:left;">User Experience</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td style="text-align:left;"><strong>Card View</strong></td><td style="text-align:left;">Retail outlets selling clothing, fashion items, and visual goods.</td><td style="text-align:left;">Image-focused, lets cashiers match visual items instantly.</td><td style="text-align:left;">Visual, engaging, and easy to select on touch screens.</td></tr><tr><td style="text-align:left;"><strong>Table View</strong></td><td style="text-align:left;">Wholesalers, spare parts dealers, and technical inventory.</td><td style="text-align:left;">High data density, displays SKUs, prices, and stock numbers.</td><td style="text-align:left;">Structured, detail-heavy, perfect for product comparisons.</td></tr><tr><td style="text-align:left;"><strong>List View</strong></td><td style="text-align:left;">Simple variations like sizes (S/M/L) or capacities (64GB/128GB).</td><td style="text-align:left;">Fast vertical scrolling, no visual distraction.</td><td style="text-align:left;">Compact, text-focused, optimized for rapid clicking.</td></tr></tbody></table><hr><h2 id="related-features" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#related-features"><span>Related Features</span></a></h2><ul><li><a href="/woocommerce-pos/products-inventory" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Product &amp; Catalog Management</a> — Set up variations and bulk assign tags in WooCommerce.</li><li><a href="/woocommerce-pos/dynamic-theme" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Dynamic Interface Theme</a> — Align variation layouts with dark mode and active display templates.</li></ul>',33)])])}]])}}]);